---
title:          "Bad Money? Witchcraft Beliefs and Fairness Views in Kenya"
date:           2025-04-01 00:01:00 +0800
selected:       false
type:           "Working Paper"
# pub:            "AEJ: Applied Economics (forthcoming)"
# pub_pre:        "Submitted"
# pub_post:       'Under review.'
pub_last:       "(Submitted)"
pub_date:       "2025"

abstract: >-
  Witchcraft beliefs shape economic attitudes in many societies. A lab experiment in Nairobi reveals divergent views: some see income from occult practices as undeserved and redistribute or destroy it, while others view it as legitimate business investment.
